Last updated: July 2026

1. INTRODUCTION

WSET Level 1 Wine Knowledge ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

2. INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT

The App is designed to function entirely offline. We do NOT collect, store, or transmit:

- Personal identification information (name, email address, phone number)
- Location data
- Device identifiers
- Usage analytics or crash reports
- Financial or payment information
- Biometric data
- Contacts or social network data

3. LOCAL STORAGE ONLY

All data generated while using the App — including exam progress, tasting notes, and application settings — is stored exclusively on your device's local storage (localStorage and IndexedDB). This data never leaves your device and is not accessible to us or any third party.

4. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The App does not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services. No data is shared with or transmitted to external servers.

5. DATA SECURITY

Since all data remains on your device, the security of your information depends on your device's built-in security measures. We recommend using standard device security practices such as screen locks and up-to-date operating systems.

6. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

The App is intended for users aged 18 and over, as it relates to alcohol education. We do not knowingly collect any information from children under the age of 18.

7. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the App and this page. Your continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

8. CONTACT US

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: ivanng611@gmail.com

9. NO DATA DELETION REQUESTS

Because we store no personal data on our servers, there is no data to delete upon request. All user data can be removed by clearing the App's data or uninstalling the App from your device.
